252
00:16:58,260 --> 00:17:02,140
so you should take advantage of these valuable opportunities.

253
00:17:02,140 --> 00:17:06,900
Who knows? It might help you in the college entrance exam.

254
00:17:07,730 --> 00:17:09,010
Don't feel overly pressured.

255
00:17:09,010 --> 00:17:11,720
Just go and see how it feels.

256
00:17:12,770 --> 00:17:14,730
I don't feel pressured.

257
00:17:14,730 --> 00:17:18,820
I just thought that before, only top students like Song Cong could take part.

258
00:17:18,820 --> 00:17:23,140
I didn't expect I'd have the opportunity too.

259
00:17:27,450 --> 00:17:29,990
Jing Xi Chi, this is your application.

260
00:17:31,380 --> 00:17:33,100
The chemistry teacher told me

261
00:17:33,100 --> 00:17:42,660
that even though you're always causing trouble in class, you have good execution skills.

262
00:17:43,120 --> 00:17:45,120
So you should take part in the competition.

263
00:17:45,120 --> 00:17:50,340
We shouldn't waste your creative mind or your talent.

264
00:17:51,860 --> 00:17:52,970
Mr. Xu.

265
00:17:52,970 --> 00:17:56,490
I know my mistake. Say no more.

266
00:17:56,490 --> 00:17:58,450
You actually admitted you're wrong?

267
00:17:58,450 --> 00:18:01,250
- Yes. 
 - Jing Xi Chi, let me say this again.

268
00:18:01,250 --> 00:18:07,690
If you dare act naughty during chemistry again, I'll get your mom to take you away.

269
00:18:07,690 --> 00:18:10,260
- Mr. Xu. 
 - You may go.

270
00:18:10,260 --> 00:18:11,580
You can have this back, sir.

271
00:18:11,580 --> 00:18:12,886
- Thank you, sir. 
 - You keep it.

272
00:18:12,886 --> 00:18:15,080
No, don't waste it.

273
00:18:15,730 --> 00:18:17,970
- Yes, Li Tian. 
 - This is my application.

274
00:18:17,970 --> 00:18:21,260
I thought you were going to apply for the English speech competition.

275
00:18:21,260 --> 00:18:22,770
How come you switched?

276
00:18:22,770 --> 00:18:25,580
I think I'm better suited for the Math competition.

277
00:18:25,580 --> 00:18:27,270
Thanks, sir.

278
00:18:32,210 --> 00:18:33,380
Can you wait for a bit?

279
00:18:33,380 --> 00:18:35,977
- I'm hungry. Why can't I start eating? 
 - Huan Er isn't here.

280
00:18:35,977 --> 00:18:38,440
I can still eat when she comes. We can start eating first.

281
00:18:38,450 --> 00:18:40,340
- Are you that hungry? 
 - I'm coming.

282
00:18:40,340 --> 00:18:41,580
Here comes the eggplant.

283
00:18:41,580 --> 00:18:44,335
Let me try it.

284
00:18:44,335 --> 00:18:45,780
- Isn't it delicious? 
 - Huan Er.

285
00:18:45,780 --> 00:18:48,200
Last night, I overheard my mom and her friends talking.

286
00:18:48,200 --> 00:18:50,512
They said that the English competition is useless for independent admissions.

287
00:18:50,512 --> 00:18:53,240
That's why Aunt Li didn't let him sign up.

288
00:18:53,240 --> 00:18:54,340
No wonder.

289
00:18:54,340 --> 00:18:57,900
Today, Mr. Xu even asked Li Tian why he changed his registration form.

290
00:18:57,900 --> 00:18:59,800
That guy has loved English since he was little.

291
00:18:59,800 --> 00:19:02,120
Back in elementary school, he even signed up for an English speech contest,

292
00:19:02,120 --> 00:19:04,490
but for some reason he didn't go in the end-

293
00:19:04,490 --> 00:19:06,857
Probably, he got shut down by Uncle Li again.

294
00:19:06,857 --> 00:19:09,490
Not "probably." Definitely.

295
00:19:09,490 --> 00:19:12,620
Last night, there was another argument upstairs about this.

296
00:19:12,620 --> 00:19:16,620
I looked it up: the two competitions are happening at the exact same time.

297
00:19:16,620 --> 00:19:18,420
So what then?

298
00:19:18,420 --> 00:19:20,660
Come on. We have to find a way to help him.

299
00:19:20,660 --> 00:19:22,530
Why do you even care what he signs up for?

300
00:19:22,530 --> 00:19:24,100
Jing Xi Chi, have you forgotten?

301
00:19:24,100 --> 00:19:26,275
He helped us steal fireworks during New Year's.

302
00:19:26,275 --> 00:19:28,580
And now you're turning your back on him?

303
00:19:28,580 --> 00:19:30,600
You're acting like a total jerk.

304
00:19:32,800 --> 00:19:34,320
What are you laughing at?

305
00:19:34,320 --> 00:19:38,155
You're the one who lit the fireworks. Don't act all innocent; that makes you a bigger jerk.

306
00:19:38,155 --> 00:19:40,030
Jerk!

307
00:19:44,970 --> 00:19:48,660
- Just focus on your own competition. 
 - Yeah, don't worry. We'll handle it.

308
00:19:49,940 --> 00:19:51,640
The eggplant is too salty.

309
00:19:51,640 --> 00:19:53,490
Don't eat it if it's bad. Leave it.

310
00:19:53,490 --> 00:19:56,470
- Here, Cong. You eat it. 
 - Let me try it.

311
00:19:56,975 --> 00:19:58,290
Tian.

312
00:19:58,290 --> 00:20:00,250
Have you got everything ready?

313
00:20:00,250 --> 00:20:03,200
- Yes. 
 - Okay.

314
00:20:08,530 --> 00:20:10,620
Coming.

315
00:20:10,620 --> 00:20:11,970
Who is it?

316
00:20:11,970 --> 00:20:13,050
Hello.

317
00:20:13,050 --> 00:20:14,450
Why are you guys here?

318
00:20:14,450 --> 00:20:16,200
Who is it?

319
00:20:16,200 --> 00:20:18,290
- Aunt Li. 
 - It's you guys.

320
00:20:18,290 --> 00:20:21,900
Aunt Li, we're here to get Li Tian for the competition.

321
00:20:21,900 --> 00:20:25,550
Xi Chi, what competition are you participating in?

322
00:20:26,400 --> 00:20:28,200
He's going there to cheer for us, Aunt Li.

323
00:20:28,200 --> 00:20:30,949
I'm actually competing in the math competition. Same exam hall as Li Tian.

324
00:20:30,949 --> 00:20:32,655
- That's right. 
 - Oh, I see.

325
00:20:32,655 --> 00:20:34,352
We'll get going then, Aunt Li.

326
00:20:34,352 --> 00:20:35,160
No need to send us off.

327
00:20:35,160 --> 00:20:36,480
We'll see ourselves out.

328
00:20:36,480 --> 00:20:39,115
- Bye, Aunt Li. 
 - Okay.

329
00:20:39,115 --> 00:20:40,180
Hurry up and go.

330
00:20:40,180 --> 00:20:41,100
- Easy, now. 
 - Move it.

331
00:20:41,100 --> 00:20:42,750
- What are you trying to do? 
 - You tell me!

332
00:20:42,750 --> 00:20:45,620
Are you kidnapping me? You two can't do this!

333
00:20:45,620 --> 00:20:46,730
Let me go!

334
00:20:46,730 --> 00:20:48,320
Let go!

335
00:20:49,860 --> 00:20:50,900
Oh, I know.

336
00:20:50,900 --> 00:20:52,970
You two must be afraid I'd get a ranking in the competition.

337
00:20:52,970 --> 00:20:55,660
I'll get bonus points for the college entrance exam and end up ranking higher than you.

338
00:20:55,660 --> 00:20:58,670
All that stuff about wanting to be friends again. That was all a lie, wasn't it?

339
00:20:58,670 --> 00:21:01,530
- Stop trying to sabotage me! 
 - Li Tian, are you crazy or what?

340
00:21:01,530 --> 00:21:03,290
You need to stop making up stories.

341
00:21:03,290 --> 00:21:04,690
Li Tian.

342
00:21:04,690 --> 00:21:06,170
Here.

343
00:21:07,340 --> 00:21:09,340
I got this pass from Mr. Xu for you.

344
00:21:09,340 --> 00:21:13,800
Whether you wish to participate in the Math or English competition is up to you.

345
00:21:15,130 --> 00:21:18,450
   

346
00:21:18,450 --> 00:21:20,210
Wait... it's real?

347
00:21:20,210 --> 00:21:22,030
Are you happy now?

348
00:21:23,420 --> 00:21:26,010
Hang on. You two must be up to something.

349
00:21:26,010 --> 00:21:28,970
- Just shut it and get moving! 
 - Let's be clear.

350
00:21:28,970 --> 00:21:32,140
You two forced me to go. I didn't go willingly.

351
00:21:32,140 --> 00:21:33,530
Do it.

352
00:21:33,530 --> 00:21:36,170
Hurry up! You don't want to be late.

353
00:22:17,200 --> 00:22:18,990
Du Man?

354
00:22:24,450 --> 00:22:27,250
The world becomes more colorful and warm. 
    

355
00:22:27,250 --> 00:22:29,380
Everyone is good to you, 
    

356
00:22:29,380 --> 00:22:31,490
and the world is full of love.

357
00:22:31,490 --> 00:22:34,650
That's all. Thank you for listening.

358
00:22:42,580 --> 00:22:45,175
Little Four-Eye...

359
00:22:45,175 --> 00:22:48,680
He was all nervous just now, and now he's up there on his own.

360
00:22:52,010 --> 00:22:53,480
Oh no.

361
00:22:54,420 --> 00:22:55,855
We might have acted too recklessly.

362
00:22:55,855 --> 00:22:57,895
Go get him back; he isn't prepared!

363
00:22:57,895 --> 00:22:59,495
Relax. He doesn't need to prepare.

364
00:22:59,495 --> 00:23:02,065
Ladies and gentlemen, good afternoon.

365
00:23:02,065 --> 00:23:04,970
I'm honored to be here today.

366
00:23:04,970 --> 00:23:09,240
The topic of my speech is "My Dream."

367
00:23:09,240 --> 00:23:15,620
My dream is to create a world where people are not forced to speak English.

368
00:23:16,860 --> 00:23:21,100
Wow, Little Four-Eye is actually pretty cool.

369
00:23:21,100 --> 00:23:23,210
He's speaking really well.

370
00:23:23,210 --> 00:23:25,130
Oh? You understood?

371
00:23:27,660 --> 00:23:29,420
Of course!

372
00:23:30,940 --> 00:23:32,900
Then what was he saying?

373
00:23:36,050 --> 00:23:37,490
Wait...

374
00:23:37,490 --> 00:23:39,470
You didn't understand?

375
00:23:44,010 --> 00:23:45,710
Thank you.

376
00:23:50,620 --> 00:23:52,810
Thank you.

377
00:23:52,810 --> 00:23:54,978
What did he just say? What was it? What did you say?

378
00:23:54,978 --> 00:23:57,320
I said thank you.

379
00:23:57,320 --> 00:23:59,340
You're welcome.

380
00:24:00,300 --> 00:24:04,530
While listening to your speech, I was reminded of the competition back in elementary school.

381
00:24:04,530 --> 00:24:06,900
I still remember the topic to this day.

382
00:24:06,900 --> 00:24:10,290
They wanted us to write about our favorite thing.

383
00:24:10,290 --> 00:24:14,050
You wrote about watching cartoons with us.

384
00:24:14,050 --> 00:24:16,660
That's why I ended up not going.

385
00:24:16,660 --> 00:24:21,380
I saw what other people wrote and thought my story was too childish.

386
00:24:21,380 --> 00:24:23,100
So it's childish watching cartoons with us?

387
00:24:23,100 --> 00:24:26,210
Then what about going up there today for a last-minute speech?

388
00:24:26,210 --> 00:24:27,730
It was made clear.

389
00:24:27,730 --> 00:24:30,050
Talk about your favorite thing, right?

390
00:24:30,050 --> 00:24:32,730
If you liked it, then that's all that matters.

391
00:24:32,730 --> 00:24:36,270
- Did you grow taller? 
 - Keep your hands to yourself.

392
00:24:38,500 --> 00:24:39,940
What was your speech about just now?

393
00:24:39,940 --> 00:24:42,380
I thought you understood.

394
00:24:44,033 --> 00:24:45,770
Yes, I understood.

395
00:24:45,770 --> 00:24:49,510
I just wanted to check if his grammar was right.

396
00:24:52,380 --> 00:24:53,900
Are you feeling better?

397
00:24:53,900 --> 00:24:55,290
Much better.

398
00:24:55,290 --> 00:24:57,250
Thanks for today.

399
00:24:57,250 --> 00:24:59,214
No worries.

400
00:24:59,214 --> 00:25:00,450
If not for you,

401
00:25:00,450 --> 00:25:02,690
I might not have been able to sit for the test.

402
00:25:02,690 --> 00:25:04,010
It's nothing.

403
00:25:04,010 --> 00:25:06,860
- Come, quick. 
 - Are you buying something?

404
00:25:12,180 --> 00:25:13,380
You're eating all these?

405
00:25:13,380 --> 00:25:15,030
Daughter.

406
00:25:15,940 --> 00:25:17,480
It's you.

407
00:25:17,480 --> 00:25:19,250
Are you two classmates?

408
00:25:19,250 --> 00:25:20,620
We're desk mates.

409
00:25:20,620 --> 00:25:23,730
Deskmates? What a coincidence. Here, take some more.

410
00:25:23,730 --> 00:25:25,260
- Hello, sir. 
 - Dad, can you get me a bag?

411
00:25:25,260 --> 00:25:27,310
Okay.

412
00:25:27,310 --> 00:25:29,450
That's your father?

413
00:25:29,450 --> 00:25:33,560
Do you remember? When you first got transferred, I told you that I had met you before.

414
00:25:33,560 --> 00:25:35,190
 How much? 

415
00:25:35,190 --> 00:25:37,340
 Ten yuan. 

416
00:25:37,340 --> 00:25:38,620
It was right here.

417
00:25:38,620 --> 00:25:40,420
Is that so?

418
00:25:40,420 --> 00:25:43,140
Here. Put the things inside.

419
00:25:43,140 --> 00:25:44,940
Sir, I can't eat all of these.

420
00:25:44,940 --> 00:25:47,420
It's fine. Take it.

421
00:25:48,820 --> 00:25:51,860
- I should pay for these. 
 - No need.

422
00:25:51,860 --> 00:25:53,610
Just take it.

423
00:25:54,690 --> 00:25:56,860
Thank you.

424
00:25:56,860 --> 00:25:58,470
I'm off.

425
00:26:06,100 --> 00:26:09,950
Jing Xi Chi, what is going on? Li Tian is competing today...

426
00:26:11,970 --> 00:26:13,210
Li Tian?

427
00:26:13,210 --> 00:26:15,330
How did the test go?

428
00:26:16,660 --> 00:26:18,690
She obviously didn't do well.

429
00:26:18,690 --> 00:26:20,210
That's no way to speak to Miss Chen.

430
00:26:20,210 --> 00:26:22,660
What happened today was her idea.

431
00:26:22,660 --> 00:26:24,050
Come on, bro.

432
00:26:24,050 --> 00:26:25,690
Come.

433
00:26:25,690 --> 00:26:26,970
Sit down, please.

434
00:26:26,970 --> 00:26:29,290
Enough with the act, Jing Xi Chi.

435
00:26:29,290 --> 00:26:31,050
It's English. Good, good!

436
00:26:31,050 --> 00:26:32,510
Go on and talk in English the whole day then.

437
00:26:32,510 --> 00:26:35,050
Sure, I can.

438
00:26:35,050 --> 00:26:36,970
Look, TV.

439
00:26:36,970 --> 00:26:38,820
I like television.

440
00:26:38,820 --> 00:26:40,490
Bro, cheers.

441
00:26:40,490 --> 00:26:42,310
Where's mine?

442
00:26:44,420 --> 00:26:46,660
Sorry.

443
00:26:46,660 --> 00:26:49,860
I don't know you come...

444
00:26:49,860 --> 00:26:51,420
So you forgot?

445
00:26:51,420 --> 00:26:52,940
- Yes. 
 - Okay.

446
00:26:52,940 --> 00:26:55,280
But... there's water in the kitchen.

447
00:26:56,960 --> 00:26:58,420
   

448
00:26:58,420 --> 00:27:01,140
This time, only Du Man from our class made it to the finals.

449
00:27:01,140 --> 00:27:02,690
If only Song Cong had participated.

450
00:27:02,690 --> 00:27:05,340
Yeah, Song Cong definitely would have made it if he had gone.

451
00:27:05,340 --> 00:27:07,250
- A bit of a shame. 
 - Yeah...

452
00:27:07,250 --> 00:27:08,290
Morning.

453
00:27:08,290 --> 00:27:09,580
Li Tian, congratulations!

454
00:27:09,580 --> 00:27:12,040
You won first place in the English speech competition.

455
00:27:14,490 --> 00:27:16,650
Congrats, Li Tian!

456
00:27:21,190 --> 00:27:23,970
You're welcome.

457
00:27:34,210 --> 00:27:35,851
   

458
00:27:35,851 --> 00:27:37,960
   

459
00:27:41,380 --> 00:27:43,340
What's the point of bringing this back to me?

460
00:27:43,340 --> 00:27:45,015
It's not even useful as a paperweight.

461
00:27:45,015 --> 00:27:47,000
Does it give extra points for admissions?

462
00:27:47,000 --> 00:27:49,180
At the very least, my English is great.

463
00:27:49,180 --> 00:27:51,453
When I go abroad in the future, I want to study English.

464
00:27:51,453 --> 00:27:55,290
You're getting more ridiculous by the day. Am I sending you abroad to study English?

465
00:27:55,290 --> 00:27:57,490
- Does that even need to be studied? 
 - Of course, it does!

466
00:27:57,490 --> 00:27:59,325
In English studies, there's also English Literature major.

467
00:27:59,325 --> 00:28:02,200
The world is a global village now. English is just a tool.

468
00:28:02,200 --> 00:28:04,340
Everyone can say at least a few words in English.

469
00:28:04,340 --> 00:28:05,860
What a lack of ambition!

470
00:28:05,860 --> 00:28:09,010
This is my life. I have the right to choose my major.

471
00:28:09,010 --> 00:28:11,660
- It's none of your business. 
 - What did you say?

472
00:28:11,660 --> 00:28:14,170
Say that to me again if you dare!

473
00:28:16,100 --> 00:28:18,230
What did he mean?

474
00:28:18,900 --> 00:28:22,050
Aren't you good at English? Why are you asking me?

475
00:28:22,050 --> 00:28:24,695
He spoke too fast. I didn't catch it.

476
00:28:24,695 --> 00:28:26,380
   

477
00:28:26,380 --> 00:28:28,030
Have water.

478
00:28:34,490 --> 00:28:36,340
Come, try this.

479
00:28:36,340 --> 00:28:38,230
It's really sweet.

480
00:28:40,340 --> 00:28:41,690
Yeah, it is.

481
00:28:41,690 --> 00:28:43,530
Then eat more.

482
00:28:43,530 --> 00:28:44,980
That's enough.

483
00:28:46,530 --> 00:28:52,660
Actually, taking part in competitions is all about participation.

484
00:28:52,660 --> 00:28:54,660
Winning or not doesn't really matter.

485
00:28:54,660 --> 00:28:56,490
Mom, what are you talking about?

486
00:28:56,490 --> 00:29:00,210
Listen up. I'm very likely to win an award in this competition.

487
00:29:00,210 --> 00:29:02,530
I've made up my mind. I want to study pharmacy.

488
00:29:02,530 --> 00:29:04,360
I'll still do it even if it's exhausting.

489
00:29:04,360 --> 00:29:06,480
Whatâ€™s gotten into you now?

490
00:29:08,190 --> 00:29:10,010
What's wrong?

491
00:29:10,010 --> 00:29:11,580
It's nothing.

492
00:29:11,580 --> 00:29:13,480
I just have a bit of a stomachache.

493
00:29:13,480 --> 00:29:16,650
Every time my period comes, my stomach hurts a lot.

494
00:29:21,580 --> 00:29:23,490
What medicine did you take? Let me see.

495
00:29:23,490 --> 00:29:26,970
   

496
00:29:26,970 --> 00:29:29,210
These two medicines shouldn't be taken together!

497
00:29:29,210 --> 00:29:32,180
I had no idea until I checked, but once I saw it, I was shocked.

498
00:29:32,180 --> 00:29:37,100
The TCM* she usually takes and the painkiller can't be taken at the same time. 
